{:itonami.blueprint/id "cloud-itonami-4912"
 :itonami.blueprint/name "Community Freight Rail Transport"
 :itonami.blueprint/isic-rev5 "4912"
 :itonami.blueprint/domain :transport/freight-rail
 :itonami.blueprint/license "AGPL-3.0-or-later"
 :itonami.blueprint/social-impact [:rail-safety :supply-resilience :decarbonization]
 :itonami.blueprint/governor :rail-freight-governor
 :itonami.blueprint/robotics true
 :itonami.blueprint/required-technologies [:robotics :identity :forms :dmn :bpmn :audit-ledger :logistics]
 :itonami.blueprint/optional-technologies [:optimization]
 :itonami.blueprint/status :public-oss
 :itonami.blueprint/maturity :implemented
 :itonami.blueprint/implemented-slice
 "RailFreight-LLM ⊣ Rail Freight Governor, langgraph-clj StateGraph
 (langgraph.graph, railfreight.operation/build), append-only audit
 ledger (railfreight.store/ledger + append-ledger!, MemStore and a
 DatomicStore backed by langchain.db). A back-office freight-rail
 OPERATIONS COORDINATION actor -- not the dispatcher, not the
 track-safety authority, not rolling-stock/locomotive control. Eight
 closed-allowlist ops, all `:effect :propose` only:
 `:log-shipment-record` / `:schedule-service-operation` /
 `:flag-track-safety-concern` / `:coordinate-maintenance` /
 `:register-hazmat-transport-scope` / `:log-inspection-record` /
 `:release-rolling-stock-from-maintenance` / `:log-reconciliation-
 record`. This corrects a fabrication found on review: an earlier
 build of this slice shipped a hardcoded `railfreight.facts` catalog
 asserting real jurisdictions' official rail-safety regulator names
 and legal citations (Japan's 鉄道事業法, US 49 C.F.R. citations, UK
 ROGS 2006, Germany's AEG, government URLs) as if the codebase itself
 were an authoritative regulatory source -- removed; `:spec-basis`/
 `:legal-basis` are now operator-supplied request keys this actor
 neither invents nor validates against any 'official' list (see
 docs/adr/0002). It also closes the three README/docs/business-
 model.md business areas an earlier R0 slice had left as an explicit
 follow-up: safety-management-system/hazmat-transport-scope
 management (`:register-hazmat-transport-scope`, HARD-blocked without
 non-blank operator-supplied evidence -- 'hazmat transport cannot
 commit without a valid hazmat-transport-scope record'),
 robotics-assisted track/rolling-stock inspection
 (`:log-inspection-record`, closed result vocabulary, gates
 `:release-rolling-stock-from-maintenance`'s own HARD check --
 'track/rolling-stock cannot be marked serviceable without a completed
 inspection record present'), and booking/reconciliation records
 (`:log-reconciliation-record`, HARD-blocked without non-blank
 evidence -- docs/business-model.md's own Trust Control
 'reconciliation records require verified evidence'). Fifteen HARD,
 permanent, un-overridable governor checks (effect-not-propose /
 op-not-allowlisted / action-not-allowlisted / scope-exclusion /
 no-spec-basis / record-not-verified / hazmat-scope-evidence-missing /
 hazmat-handling-protocol-unconfirmed / inspection-record-invalid /
 maintenance-not-open / maintenance-release-uninspected /
 reconciliation-evidence-missing / open-safety-concern /
 already-scheduled / already-coordinating), independently verified
 against Store ground truth, never the advisor's own claim. Five ops
 (`:schedule-service-operation` / `:flag-track-safety-concern` /
 `:coordinate-maintenance` / `:register-hazmat-transport-scope` /
 `:release-rolling-stock-from-maintenance`) ALWAYS escalate to a human
 via the compiled graph's `:request-approval` node
 (`interrupt-before`, checkpoint-based resume) at TWO independent
 layers (governor `high-stakes` + `railfreight.phase`'s permanent
 absence from every phase's `:auto` set) -- proven end to end by
 `test/railfreight/governor_contract_test.clj` against the REAL
 compiled graph, `test/railfreight/governor_self_trip_test.clj`
 (a dedicated regression test against a fleet-wide self-tripping
 scope-exclusion bug class, run across all eight ops), and
 `test/railfreight/phase_test.clj`. MemStore ‖ DatomicStore parity
 proven by `test/railfreight/store_contract_test.clj`. CI
 (`.github/workflows/ci.yml`, sibling-checkout pattern) was missing
 and is added in this fix. See docs/adr/0001 (original architecture)
 and docs/adr/0002 (fabrication correction + business-scope
 extension) for the full design record."}
